-- Japan Buys 98,552 Tons of U.S., Canadian Wheat in Tender
-- B y   A y a   T a k a d a
-- 2012-02-09T07:23:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-09/japan-buys-98-552-tons-of-u-s-canadian-wheat-in-tender-1-.html
Japan  bought 98,552 metric tons of
milling wheat from the U.S. and  Canada  in a regular tender
today, according to the Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry and
Fisheries.  Shipment is set from April 1 to April 30, Toshiki Tojo at
the ministry’s grain-trade division said by phone. It was the
largest purchase since Jan. 27, when the government bought
150,191 tons.  The ministry, which controls overseas purchases and
domestic sales of wheat to stabilize supply, is  Asia ’s largest
buyer as a single entity. It has bought 4.15 million tons
through regular tenders this fiscal year, compared with 5.16
million tons in the year ended March 31. Details of this week’s
tender are listed below:  To contact the reporter on this story:
